Program: Discovery
Title: The First Explorers - America and Asia
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrxx8
Last Broadcast Date: 21 September 2001
Peyoye Native American legend describes how the first explorers entering the American continent toward the end of the last Ice Age had their route blocked by ice. The hunter-gatherers from north-east Asia were undeterred.